{{for|the 1990s hip-hop group|Lo-Key?}} {{Infobox musical artist | name = Lo Key | background = solo_singer | image = LoKeyWiki.jpg | birth_name = Jonathan Thomson | birth_date = July 10th, 1984 (age 34) | birth_place = Philadelphia, PA | genre = [[Hip hop music|Hip hop]], [[Horrorcore|Horrorcore]] | occupation = Musician, visual artist, cinematographer | years_active = 1998 - Present | label = LOKE RECORDS, Shadowland Entertainment | associated_acts = The Jokerr, Redneck Souljers, A.X.E. | website = ListentoLoKey.com }} '''Jonathan Thomson''' (born July 10, 1984), known professionally by his stage name Lo Key, is an American rapper, vocalist, and creator of music and visual arts. He is the founder of the rap group MISSION : INFECT and mainly recognized for his original mask which is used as a centralized branding for his music. He is a name in [[Horrorcore|Horrorcore]], a rap subgenre.
== Career == Lo Key began his career in metal bands in the late 1990s, but eventually decided to pursue hip hop. In the early 2000s, Lo Key founded the group Temple Rain featuring members Green Vilin and Sleepy. The group released two albums before disbanding in 2004.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://radio.hearitnation.com/detroit-unplugged-replay-ft-lo-key-yd-the-vet/|title=Detroit Unplugged Replay ft/ Lo Key, YD The Vet {{!}} Hear It Nation Radio|date=2017-05-11|work=Hear It Nation Radio|access-date=2017-05-16|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://vimeo.com/38332194|title=Lokey Interview - 11/11/08|publisher=Vimeo|access-date=2017-05-16}}</ref>
In the mid-2000s, he would go on to release several solo albums including ''Follow Me'', ''The House 1'', ''The House 2'', ''SO-LO'', ''Jack Yo Beatz 1'' and ''Jack Yo Beatz 2''. In 2006, Lo Key created the group MISSION : INFECT featuring numerous underground artists including Menacide, Q-Strange, Saint Sinna, BadLuck, Grewsum, T.O.N.E-Z, Malaria, Tha Wikid One, Madd Maxxx, Green Vilin, and more. As a group, they released the projects ''Chemical Threats 1 & 2, xterM:Ination,'' and ''Asphyxiation''. Several unofficial mixtapes were also produced.{{cn|date=May 2017}}
Lo Key and MISSION : INFECT also performed 4 consecutive years at the [[Gathering of the Juggalos]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.gotjarchives.com/2006/home/?page_id=performances|title=The 7th Annual Gathering of the Juggalos 2006 - Official Website|website=www.gotjarchives.com|access-date=2017-05-16}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.juggalogathering.com/home.php?page_id=performances |title=2007 Gathering of the Juggalos - Live Performances |date=2007-08-19 |access-date=2017-05-16 |deadurl=bot: unknown |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070819232755/http://www.juggalogathering.com/home.php?page_id=performances |archivedate=2007-08-19 |df= }}</ref> Lo Key was also featured on [[Psychopathic Records]] 2008 compilation album ''Tunnel Runners'', which debuted at #21 on Billboards Top Rap Albums.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/album/360186/tunnel-runners|title=Tunnel Runners {{!}} Billboard|website=Billboard|language=en|access-date=2017-05-16}}</ref>
After a short hiatus in 2010, Lo Key would go on to create several more albums, as well as headlining his first national tour - ''The Lo Key Loves You Tour.'' <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.faygoluvers.net/v5/2013/05/lokey-loves-you-tour-starts-next-month/|title="Lokey Loves You Tour" starts next month! |publisher=Faygoluvers |access-date=2017-05-16}}</ref> In 2016 he released the album ''Jack Yo Beatz 3'', featuring a music video for the song "Nasty", as well as collaborations with [[Redneck Souljers]] and The Jokerr.<ref>{{Citation|last=lokerecords|title=Lo Key - NASTY - Official Music Video|date=2016-05-15|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_T6ndIuyjmE|accessdate=2017-05-16}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://play.spotify.com/track/3e1ohw43OwrbryoRoCRXGu?play=true|title=Spotify|website=play.spotify.com|access-date=2017-05-16}}</ref>
== Personal life == Thomson was born in [[Philadelphia]], Pennsylvania and was adopted. He grew up outside of Philadelphia and in 1999 dropped out of school to pursue a full-time music career.{{cn|date=May 2017}}
Lo Key has stated in his music that he suffered from [[Attention deficit hyperactivity disorder|attention deficit disorder]] (ADD), as well as other mental illnesses. Lo Key has also stated that he suffers from a phenomenon called [[sleep paralysis]], which he attributes to the inspiration and creation of his albums ''Shadowland'' and ''The Book of Time''.<ref>{{Citation|last=FaygoluversHeaven|title=LO KEY INTERVIEW - *FLH EXCLUSIVE* - 2016 Gathering of the Juggalos #GOTJ17|date=2016-08-05|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=53ArAOscw04|accessdate=2017-05-16}}</ref>
