[[File:Pompeii-couple.jpg|200px|right]] The so-called '''portrait of Paquius Proculus''' is a [[fresco]] currently preserved at the [[Naples National Archaeological Museum]] that was found in [[Pompeii]].
The fresco depicts a pair of middle-class Pompeians, almost certainly husband and wife. They are commonly referred to as "Paquius Proculus and his wife", due to an inscription found on the outside of the house,{{citation needed|reason=reference inscription|date=November 2018}} although a graffito inside the house later revealed the man to be Terentius Neo.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://sites.google.com/site/ad79eruption/pompeii/regio-i/reg-i-ins-7/house-of-paquius-proculus | title=House of Paquius Proculus | publisher=AD79 | accessdate=2015-10-14}}</ref> The external inscription turned out to be an election advertisement for Paquius Proculus, who had been elected [[duumviri|duovir]] some time prior to the [[eruption of Mount Vesuvius in 79 AD|eruption]].<ref name="pompeisepolta">{{cite web|url=http://pompeisepolta.com/paquio.htm|title=Casa di Paquio Proculo|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=Pompei Sepolta|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305143007/http://pompeisepolta.com/paquio.htm|archive-date=2016-03-05|dead-url=yes|accessdate=2015-10-14}}</ref>
The man in the fresco wears a toga, the mark of a Roman citizen, and holds a [[rotulus]], suggesting he is involved in local public and/or cultural events. The woman holds a [[stylus]] and [[wax tablet]], emphasizing that she is educated and literate, and is managing the bakery.{{clarify|date=April 2018}}<ref name=":0">{{cite web|url=http://cir.campania.beniculturali.it/museoarcheologiconazionale/thematic-views/image-gallery/RA106?set_language=en|title=Paquius Proculus an wife|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=Museo Archeologico Nazionale di Napoli|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171222104832/http://cir.campania.beniculturali.it/museoarcheologiconazionale/thematic-views/image-gallery/RA106?set_language=en|archive-date=2017-12-22|dead-url=yes|accessdate=2015-10-14}}</ref> It is suspected, based on the physical features of the couple, that they are [[Samnites]], which may explain the desire to show off the status they have reached in Roman society.<ref name=":0" />
