{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2015}} {{Use British English|date=December 2015}} {{BLP sources|date=January 2014}} {{Infobox writer <!-- for more information see [[:Template:Infobox writer/doc]] --> | name = Roslyn Schwartz | image = | caption = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1951|9|29}} | birth_place = [[Montreal]], [[Quebec]], [[Canada]] | home_town = [[Tunbridge Wells]], [[Kent]], [[England]] | death_date = | occupation = Author | genre = Children's Literature }} '''Roslyn Schwartz''' (born September 29, 1951) is a Canadian [[children's author]] and [[animator]].
Born in [[Montreal]], [[Quebec]], she was raised in [[Tunbridge Wells]], [[Kent]], [[England]].{{citation needed|date=February 2014}} Schwartz is the author of ''The Mole Sisters'' series,<ref name="January Mole">{{cite news |author=Monica Stark |title=Rodent Siblings |work=January Magazine |date=August 2000 |url=http://www.januarymagazine.com/kidsbooks/2moles.html |accessdate=2014-02-01}}</ref> ''The Smoker's Addictionary'' (1985), ''Rose and Dorothy'' (1981), and ''Tales from Parc la Fontaine'' (2006). ''The Mole Sisters'' was made into a T.V. cartoon series.
She also created two short animated films with the [[National Film Board of Canada]], ''I'm your Man'' and ''The Arkelope''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nfb.ca/film/arkelope|title=The Arkelope|last=Schwartz|first=Roslyn|year=1994|work=NFB.ca|publisher=National Film Board of Canada|accessdate=2009-03-30}}</ref>
Schwartz credits much of her success to her younger brother Mark,{{citation needed|date=February 2014}} creator of the traditional winter Poutinikkah festival in Quebec.
